Class CSVReader

Feature-complete CSV reader that handles everything properly, including line-breaks in text cells, varying delimiters and formatted numbers.

Cell contents are converted to their system types using ConvertValue. This can be turned off via settings.

ReadHeader()

Reads just the first row. Whether the CSV actually has a "header" cannot be determined for certain but it does check each column being of type string and not being empty/whitespace. Otherwise a FormatException is thrown.

Note: header column names convertible to either bool or any number type will fail this check if PerformTypeConversion is true.

TryDetermineTypes(UInt32)

Reads a couple rows of the CSV string and tries to find the best matching Type for each column. This works well if columns have enough data in the first couple rows. If there are no values in a certain column, the Type for this column will be 'typeof(object)' to indicate that it couldn't be determined at all.

typesAreDefinitive indicates if every column in the scanned rows only had types of one specific kind (or null) in it.
